The Bermuda legislature passed a comprehensive legislative framework that specifically addresses issues of data protection in the form of the Personal Information Protection Act 2016 (PIPA). The principal provisions of PIPA are not yet in force but are expected to come into force in 2022.
Apart from PIPA, Bermuda law recognizes a duty of confidentiality in certain circumstances under the common law.Last modified 24 Jan 2022
				
			